{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, human-on-chip platforms provide a more accurate and cost-effective alternative to traditional animal models in drug testing and toxicity assessments, addressing key challenges in the pharmaceutical industry 31, 32.",
    "Integrating DTs and on-chip systems advances precision medicine.",
    "While ML algorithms enhance DT predictions, DTs can also use rule-based or hybrid approaches.",
    "The accuracy of these models depends on the quality and relevance of input data.",
    "Collecting such data is costly and time-consuming, so on-chip systems, capable of mimicking real-world processes efficiently, are critical for refining DT models."
  ]
}